This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses temporal difference learning, which is a popular approach in reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the estimation of the Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT) of a signal, which is a common technique in signal processing and can be applied to various machine learning tasks. The paper also touches on the use of value functions, which are a fundamental concept in reinforcement learning and can be applied to a wide range of machine learning problems. Therefore, other likely sub-categories include artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
